 computation of retired pay was based."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s503/47/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, § 503(47)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted provisions that the retired grade of an officer retired under this section is the grade determined under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1370"},"text":"section 1370 of this title","children":[],"tail":" for provisions that had set the grade of officers retired under this section at the highest grade, permanent or temporary, in which he had served satisfactorily on active duty as determined by the Secretary of the Navy; or, if the Secretary determined that he had not served satisfactorily in his highest temporary grade, in the next lower grade in which he had served, but not lower than his permanent grade."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s513/17"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, § 513(17)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-08"},"text":"September 8, 1980","children":[],"tail":"” for “the date of the enactment of the Department of Defense Authorization Act, 1981” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/342"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–342","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as par. (1), inserted provision limiting applicability to officers who became members of the uniformed services before the date of the enactment of the Department of Defense Authorization Act, 1981, and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1963—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/132"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–132","children":[],"tail":" substituted “of” for “to which he would be entitled if serving on active duty in” after “2½ percent of the basic pay”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"t